title: Dale no! Logano declared 'Dega winner in controversial finish
text:
FOXSPORTS Dale no! Logano declared 'Dega winner in controversial finish Joey Logano is declared the winner in a controversial finish at Talladega. Dale Earnhardt Jr. finishes a close second, but fails to advance in the Chase for the Sprint Cup. Oct 25, 2015 at 5:06p ET 0Shares 
Joey Logano won Sunday's CampingWorld.com 500 at Talladega Superspeedway, the final race in the Contender Round of the Chase for the NASCAR Sprint Cup. 
Finishing second was Dale Earnhardt Jr ., who failed to advance out of this round. Jeff Gordon , Brad Keselowski and Carl Edwards completed the top five finishers. 
The eight-driver, three-race Eliminator Round of the Chase begins next Sunday at Martinsville Speedway. 0
